                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="rubrication" xml:id="d0">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page of Texts I and II, alternating with black lines; elements of musical notation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of punctuation signs and text dividers.&#xD;
Text I:&#xD;
Names of antiphons (mäwaśǝʾt) followed by feast or day names; names of sections of antiphons and their abbreviations (mǝlṭan); the words yǝbarǝkǝwwo, ṣälot and their abbreviations.&#xD;
Text II:&#xD;
Names of sections (wazema); names of antiphons and their abbreviations sometimes followed by the name of the day or part of the day (e.g., maḫǝlet, mäzmur, salām, ʾabun, ʾaryam, ʾǝsmä lä-ʿālam, zä-ʾamlakiyä); names of other chants sometimes followed by the name of the day (e.g., mǝlṭan, qǝnnǝwat, ʿǝzl); elements of the Table of halleluiatic chants; names of the categories of melody and their abbreviations (ʿǝzl, gǝʿǝz).</decoNote>
